<br>
She paused for a moment in the golden pool of light from a dim streetlamp, the black vinyl of her catsuit gleaming in the semi-darkness. Her black laquered nails were long and sharp, easily visible as she ran a hand through her waist-length ebony tresses. Iris couldn't resist a soft, scintillating laugh that echoed through the emptiness around her as she walked on, almost daring something else sentient to approach her from the shroudlike blackness that surrounded her. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Love sucks. Sometimes it feels good. Sometimes it's just another way to bleed.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->~Anita Blake</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
