<br>
The pale vampire slowly looks back up to Iris and slides his right hand back through his ice blue hair slowly, wetting his lips slightly.  A pair of black goggles with red lenses rest upon his forehead, his shirt a dark blue, his eyes are oddly the same color as his hair.<br>
<br>
&quot;What do you find so funny?&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkalaberia.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gwynnethdelioncourt>Gwynneth de Lioncourt</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://animatedgif.net/bulletsballs/flasharrowrt_e0.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><i>~Kalaberia Citizen~</i></span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#8B4513>(6/11/03 8:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fkalaberiafrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.jasminebecketgriffith.com/boredfairy.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Silhouettes in Vinyl</span><hr size=1> Iris just smiled, turning towards the seemingly young man, her long ebony tresses swirling around her. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Vampire...</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> her sense of smell told her. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Not bad looking, either...</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> Her unsettlingly dark eyes took him in appreciatively. <br>
<br>
&quot;I was just thinking how funny it was that I was all alone in Times Square... I remember when you couldn't get away from people here in the heart of the city...&quot; she said softly, reminiscing. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkalaberia.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gwynnethdelioncourt>Gwynneth de Lioncourt</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://animatedgif.net/bulletsballs/flasharrowrt_e0.gif" BORDER=0> at: 6/11/03 9:12 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkalaberia.showUserPublicProfile?gid=stevendeschain>Steven Deschain</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><i>~Kalaberia Citizen~</i></span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#8B4513>(6/11/03 8:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fkalaberiafrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Silhouettes in Vinyl</span><hr size=1> Steven slowly stands and stuffs his hands into his pockets.  He walks over to her and looks her up and down slowly as he walks around her.  He stops suddenly as he ends up infront of her once more and smiles a bit as he pulls his hands from his pockets and crosses his arms over his chest.<br>
