&quot;All the better... crowds are annoying.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkalaberia.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gwynnethdelioncourt>Gwynneth de Lioncourt</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://animatedgif.net/bulletsballs/flasharrowrt_e0.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><i>~Kalaberia Citizen~</i></span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#8B4513>(6/11/03 9:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fkalaberiafrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.jasminebecketgriffith.com/boredfairy.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Silhouettes in Vinyl</span><hr size=1> Iris smirked, but nodded in agreement. &quot;I concur, but I do miss the days when you could just snag someone off the street and no one'd notice they were gone...&quot; She shook her head slightly, extending a long, pale, and bare arm toward him, offering her hand with its sharpened and artificially blackened nails. <br>
<br>
&quot;Here I am, talking to you like I've known you forever, and I don't even know your name. I must be losing my touch at my old age. I'm Iris, by the way.&quot; Her voice was soft, yet not meek in the slightest. Enticing, warm, and all-encompassing, like fur sliding across bare skin. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bkalaberia.showUserPublicProfile?gid=stevendeschain>Steven Deschain</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><i>~Kalaberia Citizen~</i></span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#8B4513>(6/11/03 9:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fkalaberiafrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Silhouettes in Vinyl</span><hr size=1> Deschain smiles slowly and takes her pale hand in his own.  He squeezes her hand firmly but not too tight.<br>
<br>
&quot;Steve Deschain... pleasure to meet you Iris.&quot;<br>
<br>
He slowly takes his hand back and stuffs both of them back into his pockets, glancing around for a moment and sniffing the air.  He growls to himself slightly as he had thought he smelled a mortal but it was just his nose playing tricks on him.<br>
