emed mildly amiss. What woman, or man for that matter, in their right mind would walk through Time Square as if they owned the place?<br>
<br>
The thought came to him simply. Because they did. One at least was a vampire. The other was either a consort, or prey. Reaching out lightly with his mind, he gently brushed their surface thoughts... Both seemed resistant to his touch.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Blast!</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> he thought. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>They are both Vampires.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Smiling to himself, he stepped from the shadows in front of the couple. Dressed as he was in a semi formal suit, he looked some what out of place near the two. Like an old style Yuppy apealing to those less like himself to change their ways, and join the corperate machine. <br>
<br>
Bowing low, his soft voice echos in the empty street. &quot;Good evening, Comrades.&quot;<br>
